<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1215,2034]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1359,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Moghbeli &amp; Gharali &amp; Fekrat, 2021" authorityName="Moghbeli &amp; Gharali &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2021" box="[329,513,1359,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notiosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[329,513,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Phthiria notiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[521,612,1359,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[521,612,1359,1385]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1846" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1846" box="[955,1225,1359,1386]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis box="[955,1081,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Ph. vagans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Loew, H." box="[1089,1225,1359,1386]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="319 - 530" refId="ref2965" refString="Loew, H. (1846) Fragmente der Kenntniss der europaischen Arten einiger Dipteren Gattungen. Linnaea Entomologica, 1, 319 - 530." type="journal article" year="1846">Loew, 1846</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but in the female, it is easily distinguished by the black scutellum (yellow with a small black mark in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1846" box="[1109,1234,1395,1421]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis box="[1109,1234,1395,1421]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Ph. vagans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and in the male, 
<taxonomicName authority="Moghbeli &amp; Gharali &amp; Fekrat, 2021" authorityName="Moghbeli &amp; Gharali &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2021" box="[151,333,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notiosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,333,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Phthiria notiosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[339,428,1431,1457]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[339,428,1431,1457]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is easily distinguished from the other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[967,1060,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[967,1060,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonging to the group with short prong of first flagellomere (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Gharali, B. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[509,805,1467,1493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" pagination="1" refId="ref2852" refString="Gharali, B. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2017) Phthiria vaganoides sp. nov. (Bombyliidae, Phthiriinae, Phthiriini) from Northern Iran with the first record of Phthiria fulva Meigen, 1804 reared from a lepidopteran and description of the pupa. Zootaxa, 4300 (1), 055 - 070. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4300.1.3" type="journal article" year="2017">Gharali &amp; Evenhuis, 2017</bibRefCitation>
for grouping) by having two longitudinal dusted stripes from the anterior to the posterior margin of mesonotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="384" pageId="1" pageNumber="379" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1215,2034]" box="[199,982,1539,1566]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
