</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1215,2034]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,150,933]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="384" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1575,1601]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[281,394,1575,1602]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,179,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, male; a) holotype habit; b) head, lateral view; c) antenna, lateral view; d) pleura; e) mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026016/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1b, c</figureCitation>
) completely black; frons black, gray dusted, with long white hairs; parafacials completely black, with long white hairs; mentum gray dusted, with sparse long white hairs; ocellar tubercle prominent black, with a few white hairs; eyes in contact for about 2.0 times length of frons, contact sector of eyes medially depressed, facets of upper half of eyes enlarged; antennae (
<figureCitation box="[686,764,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,179,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, male; a) holotype habit; b) head, lateral view; c) antenna, lateral view; d) pleura; e) mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026016/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
) completely black, scape quadrate, wider than long, pedicel round, first flagellomere long, about 5 times greatest width, dorsal prong about 1.5 times length of transparent style; palpi black, proboscis black, long, 2.5 times head length. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[806,895,1755,1781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[911,1022,1755,1782]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,179,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, male; a) holotype habit; b) head, lateral view; c) antenna, lateral view; d) pleura; e) mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026016/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1d, e</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum black with two dusted longitudinal stripes from anterior margin to posterior margin of mesonotum, with sparse long white hairs marginally, length of hairs about equal to combined length of two basal antennal segments; scutellum black, gray dusted with long dense white hairs marginally; pleura completely black, gray dusted, anepisternum and katepisternum with long white hairs, laterotergite with few white hairs, halter stem and knob white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1038,1103,1899,1925]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline, uniformly microtrichose; veins blackish brown; costa reaches vein CuA1+A1; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[836,862,1953,1967]" fontSize="6" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">4+5</subScript>
originates before level of m-m crossvein; crossvein r-m beyond middle of discal cell; anal cell closed before wing margin, stalked; anal lobe broad. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1204,1249,1971,1997]" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Leg</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1264,1342,1971,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,179,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, male; a) holotype habit; b) head, lateral view; c) antenna, lateral view; d) pleura; e) mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026016/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="379">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Black; coxae and femur basally with long white hairs; tibia with a few black bristles; tarsal segments ventrolaterally with dense black bristles; empodium white, as long as claw. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[764,881,150,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[895,974,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1407,179,1918]" captionTargetId="figure-18@2.[179,1408,179,1918]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, male; a) holotype habit; b) head, lateral view; c) antenna, lateral view; d) pleura; e) mesonotum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026016/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Tergites and sternites black with sclerotized black spots, sternites with long white hairs, tergites laterally dusted triangularly.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026016" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5026016" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026016/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="380" startId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" targetBox="[179,1407,179,1918]" targetPageId="2">
