<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,222,248]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Terminalia</emphasis>
. Hypopygium black; epandrium triangular in dorsal view, with small invagination apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male terminalia of Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, a) gonocoxites, dorsal view; b) gonocoxites, ventral view; c) epandrium, dorsal view; d) phallic complex, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026020/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 2c</figureCitation>
); gonocoxites ovoid, fused medially narrowly, apicomesal process as long as gonostylus, with small bristles; gonostylus oval, apically curved, pointed (
<figureCitation box="[621,739,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male terminalia of Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, a) gonocoxites, dorsal view; b) gonocoxites, ventral view; c) epandrium, dorsal view; d) phallic complex, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026020/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Figs. 2b, c</figureCitation>
); basal aedeagal process narrow in dorsal view with two lateral rami basally, lateral aedeagal apodemes narrow (
<figureCitation box="[696,778,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male terminalia of Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, a) gonocoxites, dorsal view; b) gonocoxites, ventral view; c) epandrium, dorsal view; d) phallic complex, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026020/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
); aedeagus apically curved (
<figureCitation box="[1096,1180,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[179,1405,181,1920]" captionTargetId="figure-21@3.[179,1408,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male terminalia of Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, a) gonocoxites, dorsal view; b) gonocoxites, ventral view; c) epandrium, dorsal view; d) phallic complex, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026020/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 2d</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,367,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Female. Head</emphasis>
. (
<figureCitation box="[391,541,367,394]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[166,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, female. a) head, lateral view; b) head, dorsal view; c) pleura; d) mesonotum, dorsal view; e) abdomen, dorsolateral view; f) antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026022/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Figs. 3a, b, f</figureCitation>
) Occiput black with eye margins yellow; frons black medially, almost yellow laterally, ocellar triangle black; ocelli an equilateral triangle; oral margin black narrowly, with short scattered white hairs; antennae completely black, scape slightly longer than wide; pedicel quadrate; first antennal flagellomere long, with short dorsal prong; style transparent, shorter than antennal prong; insertion of antennae yellow above; mentum black medially; palpi black, with a few short white hairs; proboscis long, 2.5 times head length, black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,150,933]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,288,547,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[304,414,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[166,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, female. a) head, lateral view; b) head, dorsal view; c) pleura; d) mesonotum, dorsal view; e) abdomen, dorsolateral view; f) antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026022/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 3c, b</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum glossy black, bare, with two grey dusted stripes extended from anterior margin to posterior margin of mesonotum, laterally yellow, postpronotum white, scutellum black, bare; pleura black except following: anteroventral corner of anepisternum, upper margin of katepisternum and meron; lower margin of anepimeron and laterotergite; halter stem and knob white. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[844,889,655,681]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Leg</emphasis>
. Coxae black with scattered white hairs, femora black, tibiae black with small black bristles, tarsi black, empodium yellow, as long as claw. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1161,1226,690,716]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1241,1322,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[327,1258,182,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[327,1261,181,1940]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Wing and female terminalia. a) wing; b) female terminalia; c) female terminalia in closer view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026026" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026026/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, uniformly microtrichose; veins blackish brown; costa reaches vein CuA1+A1; R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1060,1086,745,759]" fontSize="6" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">4+5</subScript>
originates before level of m-m crossvein; crossvein r-m beyond middle of discal cell; anal cell closed, stalked; anal lobe wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1211,1328,762,788]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1342,1423,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[166,1422,181,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-18@4.[166,1422,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Phthiria notiosa sp. nov,, female. a) head, lateral view; b) head, dorsal view; c) pleura; d) mesonotum, dorsal view; e) abdomen, dorsolateral view; f) antenna, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026022/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
). Tergites glossy black with posterior margins yellow; sternites black, bare. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[969,1100,798,824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1115,1236,799,826]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1964,1988]" captionTargetBox="[327,1258,182,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[327,1261,181,1940]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Wing and female terminalia. a) wing; b) female terminalia; c) female terminalia in closer view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026026" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026026/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="384">Figs. 4b–c</figureCitation>
). Furca consisting of two parallel bars; common spermathecal duct short, membranous; basal ducts membranous; sperm pump narrower than apical ducts, striated, with apical valve absent, apical ducts sclerotized, curved; basal sac membranous, round, spermathecal reservoir well sclerotized, cone-shaped, slightly curved, about 3 times capsule length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
