<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="385" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,150,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Distribution.</emphasis>
This species is currently known only from Bondar-Hanza village belonging to Hanza city. This city is in a small part of 
<collectingRegion box="[427,623,186,213]" country="Iran" name="Kerman" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Kerman province</collectingRegion>
in the south of 
<collectingCountry box="[801,850,187,213]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Iran</collectingCountry>
. Specimens were collected by using white pan traps scattered in a mountainous area (
<figureCitation box="[520,586,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,250,2014,2038]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,957,1990]" captionTargetId="figure-369@6.[170,1417,957,1991]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. Habitat of Phthiria notiosa sp. nov, Hanza village (Kerman province, the south of Iran)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5026028" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5026028/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) dominated mostly by plant in 
<taxonomicName box="[937,1060,222,248]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Besser" authorityName="Besser" authorityYear="1836" box="[1076,1351,222,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Artemisia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sieberi">
<emphasis box="[1076,1268,222,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Artemisia sieberi</emphasis>
Besser
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuntz" authorityName="Kuntz" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Hertia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Hertia intermedia</emphasis>
Kuntz
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Boiss" authorityName="Boiss" box="[414,774,258,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Astragalus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fasciculifolius">
<emphasis box="[414,702,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Astragalus fasciculifolius</emphasis>
Boiss
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName box="[838,942,258,284]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Apiaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authority="(Schlecht)" baseAuthorityName="Schlecht" box="[960,1298,258,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ferulago" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angulate">
<emphasis box="[960,1171,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ferulago angulate</emphasis>
(Schlecht)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Boiss. et Buhse)" baseAuthorityName="Boiss. et Buhse" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apiaceae" genus="Ferula" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oopoda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ferula oopoda</emphasis>
(Boiss. et Buhse)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="385" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,330,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Etymology</emphasis>
. The name of new species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityName="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2021" box="[636,1124,330,356]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notiosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[636,818,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Phthiria notiosa</emphasis>
Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1130,1219,330,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1130,1219,330,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is derived from the Greek “νότιος” meaning “southern” referring to the distribution of the new species being confined to the southern parts of 
<collectingCountry box="[243,292,403,429]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,753]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,445,438,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Engel, O." box="[452,598,438,464]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" pagination="97 - 144" refId="ref2681" refString="Engel, O. (1933) Bombyliidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. IV (3). E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 97 - 144." type="book chapter" year="1933">Engel (1933)</bibRefCitation>
was the first who presented a key to almost all known species of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[151,244,474,500]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,244,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Palaearctic Region. Using Engel’s key, the male specimens of the new species run to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="vagans" subSpecies="pallescens">
<emphasis box="[1263,1294,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1308,1387,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">vagans</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[151,270,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">pallescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[271,275,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">,</emphasis>
but 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityName="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2021" box="[322,808,510,536]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notiosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[322,504,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Phthiria notiosa</emphasis>
Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[813,902,510,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[813,902,510,536]" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinguished by two longitudinal dust stripes (absent in 
<taxonomicName box="[268,567,546,573]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="vagans" subSpecies="pallescens">
<emphasis box="[268,299,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[313,392,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">vagans</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[450,567,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">pallescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the color of halter knob, which is completely yellow (with a brown spot dorsally in 
<taxonomicName box="[280,582,582,609]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="vagans" subSpecies="pallescens">
<emphasis box="[280,311,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[326,405,583,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">vagans</emphasis>
ssp. 
<emphasis box="[465,582,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">pallescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The female specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityName="Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat" authorityYear="2021" box="[898,1395,582,608]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="notiosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[898,1082,582,608]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Phthiria notiosa</emphasis>
Gharali, Mogbeli &amp; Fekrat
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="7" pageNumber="385" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
run to couplet 23 where 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1915" box="[481,593,618,645]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incisa">
<emphasis box="[481,512,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ph</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[526,593,619,644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">incisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1846" box="[648,772,618,645]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vagans">
<emphasis box="[648,679,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="385">Ph</emphasis>
. 
